Their circulatory system is guts floating in blood. The heart is a pulsating tube, sometimes with an extension to direct the current better. Squishing bugs makes blood flow impossible. Their heart can not circulate the fluid with their body cavity broken open.

Their respiration system is tubes all over their body opening to the outside and they partially rely on body movement to keep things flowing. There's some help from inflation/deflation within the tracheal tubes but mostly the bug needs to be able to idly pulsate to breath. They can't do that with their body cracked open.
